Arkansas Gov . 
  Asa Hutchinson said he won't sign a religious freedom bill because it 'does not mirror the federal law' His son Seth Hutchinson signed a petition asking him not to do so . 
  The White House said the bill could 'be used to justify discriminating against individuals because of who they love' Hutchinson is sending the bill back to the state legislature for amendments that would make it more in line with the 1993 federal Religious Freedom Restoration Act . 
  He said his son convinced him to send it back to lawmakers . 
  Seth said he and his father 'have political disagreements'